herbs
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:acceleration; (horse)power (of an engine, a car etc),  esp. in give her the herbs give her the gun, the throttle; sometimes feed her the herbs.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1952 Wellington motorist. This model's got plenty of herbs all right. ca1953 J.H. Brownlee, K. Cullinane ca1961 Les Cleveland give her the herbs `increase acceleration in a car, motor cycle, or engine of any kind.' 1953 17 M A38 Thames DHS 6 HERBS: GIVE HER (GIV' 'A) THE HERBS 1984 14 F E144 Wgton Girls C. 6 REV UP THE HERBS
