Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGiLL
Vol / Page:  56
Edition:
Quote:  herbs power/speed/ratio, phr. give him/her/it herbs or  plenty of herbs usually suggestion you depress car accelerator to the floor or its maximum; originally sluggish horses were given more herbs, or oats. NZA.
